# Hookbase webhook handler — Express + {{PROVIDER_LABEL}}

A minimal Express server that verifies {{PROVIDER_LABEL}} webhook signatures and prints incoming events.

## Setup

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env
# edit .env and set your signing secret
npm run dev
```

The server listens on `http://localhost:3000/webhook` by default.

## Pointing Hookbase at it

In dev, expose your local server through a Hookbase tunnel:

```bash
hookbase listen 3000
```

Then configure your Hookbase destination URL to `<your-tunnel-url>/webhook`.

{{SOURCE_URL}}

## Signature verification

Uses the `{{HEADER_NAME}}` header. Always set `{{ENV_VAR_NAME}}` in production — without it requests are rejected.
